Number of illness per million servings of egg (lightly cooked or weel-cooked)%%00010# - Probability of illness when ingesting a random serving%%00010%%00010%%00010library(mvtnorm)%%00010library(mc2d)%%00010%%00010# Final parameters:%%00010minD<-c(minD1,minD4,minD5,minD6,minD8,minD10)%%00010maxD<-c(maxD1,maxD4,maxD5,maxD6,maxD8,maxD10)%%00010modeD<-c(modeD1,modeD4,modeD5,modeD6,modeD8,modeD10)%%00010minT<-c(minT1,minT4,minT5,minT6,minT8,minT10)%%00010maxT<-c(maxT1,maxT4,maxT5,maxT6,maxT8,maxT10)%%00010modeT<-c(modeT1,modeT4,modeT5,modeT6,modeT8,modeT10)%%00010%%00010parm=cbind(minD,modeD,maxD,minT,modeT,maxT)%%00010%%00010res=matrix(rep(0,3*sim),ncol=3)%%00010%%00010for (j in 1:sim) {%%00010 T=41.2 # temperature%%00010 for (i in 1:nrow(parm)) {%%00010 Ti=T[length(T)]%%00010 Ts=rpert(1,min=minT[i],mode=modeT[i],max=maxT[i])%%00010 times=floor(rpert(1,min=minD[i],mode=modeD[i],max=maxD[i]))%%00010 krs<-ifelse(i==1,rpert(1,min=0.8,mode=0.9,max=1),%%00010 ifelse(i==2,rpert(1,min=25,mode=27,max=30),%%00010 rpert(1,min=0.066,mode=0.1,max=0.134)))%%00010 # reduction of the internal temperature of egg%%00010 T=c(T,Ts+(Ti-Ts)*exp(-krs*(1:times)))%%00010 } # end of for de i%%00010 a=2.0872%%00010 b=-0.042579%%00010 Tmin=6.29%%00010 Topt=40.11%%00010 Tmax=43.46%%00010 kopt=1.6%%00010 ft=cumsum(1/((10^(a+b*T))*24)) %%00010 gammaT = ((T - Tmax) * (T - Tmin) ^ 2) / %%00010 ((Topt - Tmin) * ((Topt - Tmin) * (T - Topt) - (Topt - Tmax) * (Topt + Tmin - 2 * T)))%%00010 NCD=sum((ft>=1)*gammaT*kopt) # growth rate (log10 CFU/g per hour)%%00010 TRMV=which(ft>=1)[1] # give TRVM=1 if breakdown (ft>=1)%%00010 matres=cbind(min(NCD,9),TRMV,round(length(T)/24,1))%%00010 res[j,]<-matres%%00010 %%00010} #end of for de j%%00010#c0 : initial contamination%%00010c0=1+rpois(sim,7)%%00010dosecru=c0*(10^res[,1])%%00010doselcuit=c0*(10^res[,1])*(10^(-rnorm(sim,2,0.5)))%%00010dosebcuit=c0*(10^res[,1])*(10^(-rnorm(sim,12,1)))%%00010beta=53.33348955%%00010alpha=0.134586035%%00010probacru=1-(1+dosecru/beta)^(-alpha)%%00010probalcuit=1-(1+doselcuit/beta)^(-alpha)%%00010probabcuit=1-(1+dosebcuit/beta)^(-alpha)%%00010data=data.frame(res,c0,dosecru,probacru,probalcuit,probabcuit)%%00010names(data)<-c("NCD","TRMV","AGE","CI","CC","Pcru","Plcuit","Pbcuit")%%00010%%00010# NCD: growth rate (log10 CFU/g per hour)%%00010# TRMV: yolk membrane breakdown time (days)%%00010# AGE : age of eggs (day)%%00010# CI: Initial contamination: number of S. Enteredis (log10 CFU)%%00010# CC: Dose in uncooked eggs (log10 CFU)%%00010# Pcru: Probability of illness per S. Enteritidis-contaminated serving of uncooked egg%%00010# Plcuit: Probability of illness per S. Enteritidis-contaminated serving of lightly cooked egg%%00010# Pbcuit: Probability of illness per S. Enteritidis-contaminated serving of well-cooked egg%%00010%%00010%%00010out=data%%00010#head(out)%%00010#tail(out)%%00010%%00010# barplot%%00010Rlcuit=(1-freqcuisson)*prevalence*round(1E6*(mean(out[,7])),2) # Rlcuit: Number of illness per million servings of lightly cooked egg%%00010Rbcuit=freqcuisson*prevalence*round(1E6*(mean(out[,8])),2) # Rbcuit: Number of illness per million servings of well-cooked egg%%00010%%00010# plot%%00010Rlcuit_1=prevalence*out[,7] # Rlcuit_1: probability of illness when ingesting a serving of lightly cooked egg%%00010Rbcuit_1=prevalence*out[,8] # Rbcuit_1: probability of illness when ingesting a serving of well-cooked egg%%00010Risque=freqcuisson*Rbcuit_1+(1-freqcuisson)*Rlcuit_1 # Probability of illness when ingesting a random serving of egg%%00010
